.TH AEROMUX 1 "2026-03-19" "aeromux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
Aeromux \- multi-SDR Mode S and ADS-B demodulator and decoder
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aeromux
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Aeromux receives 1090 MHz ADS-B and Mode S signals from one or more RTL-SDR
devices, decodes aircraft transponder messages, and provides real-time aircraft
tracking via a terminal UI, REST API, and network streaming protocols (Beast,
SBS BaseStation, JSON).
.PP
Aeromux supports multiple simultaneous SDR devices and Beast TCP input sources.
Frames from all active sources are automatically aggregated and deduplicated by
the tracker.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B daemon
Run Aeromux as a background service for continuous, unattended operation.
Decoded aircraft data is made available over TCP protocols (Beast, SBS, JSON)
and a REST API. This is the primary mode for production deployments and headless
systems such as Raspberry Pi.
.TP
.B live
Launch an interactive terminal interface that displays tracked aircraft in real
time. Provides a sortable, searchable aircraft list and a detail view for
individual aircraft. Supports the same input sources as the daemon command.
.TP
.B database update
Download or update the aircraft metadata database from the aeromux-db GitHub
releases. Integrity verification is performed automatically during download and
update operations. The database enriches tracked aircraft with registration,
operator, manufacturer, and type information.
.TP
.B database info
Display the currently installed database version and statistics, including the
number of records and the date of the last update.
.TP
.B device
List all RTL-SDR USB receivers detected on the system. Useful for identifying
device indices before configuring the sdrSources section of the YAML file.
.TP
.B version
Display the Aeromux version number and runtime information.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
These options are available on all commands:
.TP
.BI \-\-config " path"
Path to the YAML configuration file. Default:
.IR aeromux.yaml .
.TP
.BI \-\-log\-level " level"
Logging verbosity: Verbose, Debug, Information, Warning, Error, or Fatal.
.TP
.BI \-\-database " path"
Path to the aircraft metadata database directory. Specifying this option
implicitly enables database enrichment.
.SH INPUT OPTIONS
The
.B daemon
and
.B live
commands share the same input model. Aeromux can receive data from local
RTL-SDR devices, from remote Beast TCP sources, or from both simultaneously.
.TP
.B \-\-sdr\-source
Enable RTL-SDR device input using the sdrSources defined in the YAML file.
Implied when no Beast sources are configured.
.TP
.BI \-\-beast\-source " HOST:PORT"
Connect to a Beast TCP source. Can be specified multiple times for multiple
sources. If the port is omitted, it defaults to 30005. CLI Beast sources
override any beastSources defined in the YAML file.
.SH DAEMON OPTIONS
These options are specific to the
.B daemon
command.
.TP
.BI \-\-beast\-output\-port " port"
TCP port for Beast binary protocol output. Default: 30005.
.TP
.BI \-\-beast\-output\-enabled " bool"
Enable or disable Beast output. Default: true.
.TP
.BI \-\-sbs\-output\-port " port"
TCP port for SBS/BaseStation text protocol output. Default: 30003.
.TP
.BI \-\-sbs\-output\-enabled " bool"
Enable or disable SBS output. Default: false.
.TP
.BI \-\-json\-output\-port " port"
TCP port for streaming JSON output. Default: 30006.
.TP
.BI \-\-json\-output\-enabled " bool"
Enable or disable JSON output. Default: false.
.TP
.BI \-\-api\-port " port"
TCP port for the REST API. Default: 8080.
.TP
.BI \-\-api\-enabled " bool"
Enable or disable the REST API. Default: true.
.TP
.BI \-\-bind\-address " ip"
Network interface to bind all listeners to. Default: 0.0.0.0.
.TP
.BI \-\-mlat\-enabled " bool"
Enable or disable MLAT input from mlat-client. Default: true.
.TP
.BI \-\-mlat\-input\-port " port"
TCP port for receiving MLAT Beast data. Default: 30104.
.TP
.BI \-\-receiver\-uuid " uuid"
Receiver UUID for MLAT triangulation and receiver identification. Must be a
valid RFC 4122 UUID. Each receiver must have a unique UUID.
.SH DEVICE OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Show detailed tuner parameters including supported gains and frequency range
for each detected device. This can help when fine-tuning the gain settings in
your configuration.
.SH VERSION OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Display verbose version information including commit hash, .NET runtime version,
license, and repository URL.
.SH CONFIGURATION PRIORITY
Every setting follows the resolution order: CLI parameter > YAML configuration >
built-in default. This priority is applied per-setting, so you can rely on the
YAML file for most of your configuration while selectively overriding specific
values on the command line.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Run as a daemon with SDR input from the YAML configuration:
.RS
.nf
aeromux daemon \-\-config /etc/aeromux/aeromux.yaml
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run as a daemon with a remote Beast source:
.RS
.nf
aeromux daemon \-\-beast\-source 192.168.1.100:30005 \-\-config aeromux.yaml
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run as a daemon with both SDR and Beast input:
.RS
.nf
aeromux daemon \-\-sdr\-source \-\-beast\-source 192.168.1.100:30005 \-\-config aeromux.yaml
.fi
.RE
.PP
Launch the interactive terminal interface:
.RS
.nf
aeromux live \-\-config aeromux.yaml
.fi
.RE
.PP
Download or update the aircraft metadata database:
.RS
.nf
aeromux database update \-\-database /var/lib/aeromux/
.fi
.RE
.PP
List detected RTL-SDR devices:
.RS
.nf
aeromux device
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/aeromux
Self-contained executable.
.TP
.I /etc/aeromux/aeromux.yaml
Default configuration file for the system-installed service.
.TP
.I /var/lib/aeromux/
Aircraft metadata database storage directory.
.TP
.I /var/log/aeromux/
Log file directory.
.SH SYSTEMD
When installed as a system package, aeromux runs as a systemd service under a
dedicated
.B aeromux
user.
.PP
Enable and start the service:
.RS
.nf
sudo systemctl enable \-\-now aeromux
.fi
.RE
.PP
Check service status:
.RS
.nf
systemctl status aeromux
.fi
.RE
.PP
View logs:
.RS
.nf
journalctl \-u aeromux \-f
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.UR https://github.com/aeromux/aeromux
Aeromux on GitHub
